headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 16 of his 38 points in the fourth quarter and overtime, and Josh Hart had the 11th triple-double of his career as the New York Knicks beat the Philadelphia 76ers 125-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 16 of his 38 points in 4th quarter and OT as Knicks beat 76ers 125-119

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett had 22 points and 10 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors snapped a 10-game losing streak against Boston with a 110-97 victory over the Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett stars as Raptors beat Celtics 110-97 to snap 10-game losing streak against Boston

headlines.description: — Keaton Wallace had a career-high 27 points and the short-handed Atlanta Hawks beat the Chicago Bulls 110-94 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keaton Wallace scores career-high 27 points to help the Hawks beat the Bulls, 110-94

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 30 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points and 11 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks capitalized on a fast start for the second straight night and trounced the Orlando Magic 122-93 on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 30 as Bucks roll to a 122-93 victory over Magic

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 30 points, Trey Murphy III had a disputed block of Spencer Dinwiddie's layup for the lead with 4 seconds left and the New Orleans Pelicans outlasted the injury-depleted Dallas Mavericks 119-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray scores 30 points as the Pelicans outlast the injury-depleted Mavericks 119-116

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 21 points and 12 assists to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 129-115 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant's 21-point, 12-assist performance carries Grizzlies past Wembanyama and the Spurs 129-115

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 34 points, Alperen Sengun had 20 points, nine rebounds and eight assists and the Houston Rockets beat the short-handed Denver Nuggets 128-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green and Sengun help the Rockets beat the short-handed Nuggets 128-108

headlines.description: — Mark Williams scored a career high 31 points and had 13 rebounds to help the Charlotte Hornets beat the Utah Jazz 117-112 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mark Williams scores career-high 31 points in the Hornets' 117-112 victory over the Jazz

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry made seven 3-pointers and scored 31 points to help the Golden State Warriors stave off a furious comeback Wednesday by the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors fend off Timberwolves 116-115 behind Curry's 31 points to climb back to .500

events.name: Miami Heat at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Rui Hachimura scored 23 points and Anthony Davis had 22 points and 11 rebounds as the Los Angeles Lakers snapped a three-game skid with a 117-108 victory over the Miami Heat on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hachimura and Davis help Lakers end 3-game skid with a 117-108 win over the Heat

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 23 points, James Harden added 21 and the Los Angeles Clippers had the largest margin of victory in franchise history, routing the Brooklyn Nets 126-67 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout Nets 126-67 for largest margin of victory in team history
